categories.title: Recent Pull Requests in the elizaOS/eliza Repository

content.text:
The elizaOS/eliza repository has seen several recent pull requests that add new features and improvements:

1. Support for Greenfield chain was added to the BNB plugin (PR #3621)

2. Version 0.25.8 was released with a version bump (PR #3631)

3. Multiple PRs (#3635, #3634, #3638) were submitted to add Toby voice functionality to various features including group chats and actions

4. A new Paradex DEX plugin was added (PR #3641)

5. Multi-tenancy support was implemented by adding an 'agent' table and renaming the 'user' table to 'entity' (PR #3637)

6. The langchain dependency for text splitting was removed (PR #3642), likely to reduce dependencies or improve performance

categories.title: Recent GitHub Issues in the elizaOS/eliza Repository

content.text:
Several issues have been recently reported in the elizaOS/eliza GitHub repository:

1. Issue #3628: A user reported that the agent isn't responding based on the provided knowledge.

2. Issue #3627: A feature request to add Paradex DEX Integration for Automated Trading.

3. Issue #3626: A user is seeking help with WebService usage.

4. Issue #3639: A type error where the Type Alias "Adapter" is not defined.

These issues span various aspects of the eliza system, from knowledge-based responses to integration features, usage help, and type definition problems.

Over the past two days (February 21-23, 2025), the elizaos/eliza repository showed significant activity. On February 21-22, there were 13 new pull requests with 9 merged, 4 new issues, and 29 active contributors. Activity decreased on February 22-23, with only 5 new pull requests (none merged), 1 new issue, and 9 active contributors.
